Location of Dominica Dominica is a sovereign island country.[1] Bananas and other agriculture dominate Dominica's economy, and nearly one-third of the labour force works in agriculture. This sector, however, is highly vulnerable to weather conditions and to external events affecting commodity prices. Traditional sheep fur hat of Central and South Asia Maulana Abul Kalam Azad, an Indian nationalist leader, who was also the longest serving President of the Indian National Congress wearing Karakul hat. A Karakul hat (Dari/Urdu/Pashto/Uzbek/Kashmiri: قراقلی), sometimes spelled as Qaraqul hat, also called Uzbek hat[1] and Jinnah Cap.[2][3] It is a hat made from the fur of the Qaraqul breed of sheep.
